<section class="info-section">
  <h2>What is a Rent Receipt?</h2>
  <p>A rent receipt is a written record that proves a tenant has paid rent to their landlord for a specific rental period. It's a simple but important document used worldwide for legal protection, tax filings, and record-keeping.</p>

  <h3>Why landlords need rent receipts</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Legal proof of rental income for tax purposes</li>
    <li>Protection in case of payment disputes</li>
    <li>Required by law in many states and countries</li>
    <li>Professional record-keeping for property management</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why tenants need rent receipts</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Proof of payment if a landlord ever claims rent wasn't received</li>
    <li>Supporting document for HRA tax deductions (India), Schedule E, or local rental tax credits</li>
    <li>Required by some employers for housing allowance claims</li>
    <li>Useful for visa applications, loan applications, and rental history verification</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What to include on a rent receipt</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Tenant's full name</li>
    <li>Landlord's name or company</li>
    <li>Property address</li>
    <li>Rental period covered (start and end dates)</li>
    <li>Amount paid and currency</li>
    <li>Payment method (cash, bank transfer, check, etc.)</li>
    <li>Receipt number and date issued</li>
    <li>Landlord's signature</li>
  </ul>
</section>

